# Security & secrets

- **Never** put `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, or `RESEND_API_KEY` in `NUXT_PUBLIC_*` or client code.
- Server-only keys belong in `runtimeConfig` private fields or `process.env` read only in `server/`.
- Do not log `.env` values, JWTs, invite tokens, or resume text in production paths.
- `.env` and `server/assets/template.docx` are gitignored — never commit them.

When adding env vars, update `.env.example` with placeholders only.
